criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Patients aged over 18 years old;

          -  Patients with ASA status 1, 2 or 3;

          -  Patients who underwent surgery with general anaesthesia and intubation;

          -  written consent.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Patients under corticosteroids;

          -  Pregnant women;

          -  Patient with at least two difficult intubation criteria or a limited mouth opening
             (under 2cm), difficult airway management history, upper airway tumour or cervical
             rachis trauma;

          -  Patients who had an otorhinolaryngologic infection in the last month, an intubation or
             endoscopy of upper airway in the last 48 hours, vomiting in the last 24 hours, a
             gastric tube in the last 24 hours or throat symptoms prior to surgery;

          -  Patients scheduled for a surgery implying a manipulation of upper airways;

          -  Patient scheduled for a surgery > 2 hours.
